      <exercise id="fs-id1169737780474" type="problems-exercises">
        <problem id="fs-id1169737780478">
    <para id="import-auto-id1169738077207">A hand-driven tire pump has a piston with a 2.50-cm diameter and a maximum stroke of 30.0 cm. (a) How much work do you do in one stroke if the average gauge pressure is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>40</m:mtext><m:mi>×</m:mi><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext> N/m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> (about 35 psi)? (b) What average force do you exert on the piston, neglecting friction and gravitational force?</para></problem></exercise>


